# VP-Hub Revit licensing (always-on policy)

Authoritative detail: [`docs/AGENTS.md`](../../docs/AGENTS.md).

## Non-negotiable

- Revit add-in **must not** call the cloud Worker/API directly.
- **No** access tokens, refresh tokens, secrets, or private grant-signing keys in the add-in.
- Talk to the **local Windows agent** only via **named-pipe IPC** (`NamedPipeAgentClient.CanRunAsync`).
- **Never** trust `Allowed == true` without **ES256 proof verification** (`RevitLicenseProofVerifier`).
- Pin publisher: `ExpectedPublisherId`, `ExpectedKid`, `ExpectedPublisherPublicKeyPem`, optional `ExpectedAudienceServerId`; bind `ProductCode`.
- Enforce freshness: exact `RequestNonce`; timestamp echo within skew.
- On IPC failure, `Allowed == false`, or verification failure: **deny** — no fallback allow.
- Cache verified OK in memory (30–120 seconds typical).
- Local diagnostics: `VpHubPluginFileLog` → `%LocalAppData%\VP-Hub\logs\{productCode}.log` (see `docs/logging-redaction-policy.md`).

## TFM / IPC matrix

| Revit years | TFM | IPC package |
|-------------|-----|-------------|
| 2023–2024 | net48 | `LicensingSystem.Agent.Ipc.Revit` |
| 2025+ | net8.0-windows | `LicensingSystem.Agent.Ipc` |

## Packaging (net48)

- `Contents/<year>/` must be **self-contained** (all runtime `*.dll` from build output).
- Minimum for licensed products: `System.Text.Json.dll`, `LicensingSystem.Agent.Ipc.Revit.dll`, `LicensingSystem.Contracts.dll`, `LicensingSystem.Revit.Licensing.dll`.
- Register `PluginAssemblyResolver` in `OnStartup` before licensing/IPC on net48.

